Behavior Modification Plan [id=fba2_plan_section]
---------------------------

JJ: I asked AI to generate two complete plans — one assuming escape, one assuming sensory. That way we can see why getting the function right actually matters. [face=explaining]

::fba2_plan_selection [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar3auto label="Choose Best Plan"]

Annie: Honestly, some of the sensory ideas sound really nice — calming music, weighted blankets. I could see those helping Johnny relax. [face=explaining]

JJ: They do sound nice. But which plan actually fits what we know about Johnny?

--- wait @fba2_plan_choice.submitCount > 0 ---

Escape Plan Review [id=fba2_escape_plan_review]
-------------------

::fba2_escape_plan_display [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar3auto label="Review Escape Plan Details"]

JJ: There's a lot in here. Not everything makes equal sense for Johnny's specific situation, but I really like the timer idea — using a timer to show when each routine step begins and ends. That's a solid antecedent strategy. [face=explaining]

Lin: I agree. And on the consequence side, not reinforcing the escape — no chasing, no bargaining — makes a lot of sense.

Annie: Wait — "not reinforcing"? He knocked over a lamp last time. We can't just ignore him running through the house. [face=concerned]

Lin: We're not saying ignore him completely — you still keep bedtime safe. The point is to stop chasing and bribing, because those are what reinforce the running. You change the antecedents so he doesn't need to escape, and you don't let the running "work" by delaying bedtime. [face=serious]

Annie: Okay, that's an important distinction. What parts of the plan stand out to you?

--- wait @fba2_plan_likes.value ---

Checking Understanding of Plans [id=fba2_plan_check]
--------------------------------

::fba2_sensory_plan_check [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar3auto label="Check: Why Not the Sensory Plan?"]

Annie: But some of the sensory ideas are genuinely good strategies. Calming music before bed, a predictable sensory environment... wouldn't those help any kid? [face=explaining]

Lin: They might be nice supports, but they can't be the core plan. Johnny's function is escape — a weighted blanket isn't going to solve the problem if the reason he's running away is to avoid going to bed. You could add calming music as part of an antecedent strategy, but only if the plan is built around escape first. [face=serious]

Annie: So: wrong function for the core plan, but nice supports on top of the right one. [face=smile]

--- wait @fba2_sensory_check_choice.submitCount > 0 ---

